Homecoming Update:
With the forcasted rain, we have some alternative plans ready in case they are necessary.
We will decide by 3:15 about the parade. Hopefully, we have our traditional parade at 4pm.
The Homecoming Ceremony is scheduled for 6:30. We will make a decision at 6pm based on the current weather situation and the forcasted weather. The alternative time for the ceremony would be halftime.
Our hope is to maintain our traditional parade at 4pm and homecoming ceremony at 6:30pm. Please check our social media outlets for updates.

Chelsea Public Schools Athletics COVID Plan
Chelsea Public Schools has implemented the following protocols with the intent of mitigating risk of exposure to entrance gate attendants, concession workers, and fans.
It is strongly recommended that fans practice social distancing and wear face coverings
Donation boxes will be placed at each entrance with a suggested donation of $5 per person
Concessions will be limited to drinks and pre-packaged items
All students/children 8th grade and below must be accompanied by an adult

post_text:
Nowata High School State and National Assessment Selection

Nowata Schools has chosen the ACT as part of the state contract with the Oklahoma State Department of Education and ACT. We will administer this assessment in the Spring of 2021 to all eligible 11th-grade students. This will be at no cost to the students or families. Additional information about the ACT can be found at https://www.act.org/content/act/en/products-and-services/the-act/scores/act-vs-sat.html.

Parents and students may provide meaningful input regarding the district’s selection by filling out this form. https://forms.gle/uJpsoUxohmsRT6g59

post_text: I would personally like to thank the community for your kindness during this unusual time for our school. I have watched our plan to reopen the school, and I have not observed one unkind comment. I truly appreciate that. I have been anxious about doing the right thing for our students. Through the years, all students have been so important to me. Our children are our most precious gift. The staff at NES and I talk about flexibility and grace at every meeting. Thank you for extending it to us. I am a phone call away for any concern you might have. Thank you again, Sherry Campbell

post_text:
Graduation Update:
After speaking with local authorities,
At this time, no restirictions on numbers who can attend are in place.
You will be expected to social distance yourself.
Taking tempratures at the entracnes is being considered.
All those taking part in the ceremony will be seated from the 50 yardline to the South. That leaves from the 50 yardline to the North for guests to bring chairs if they desire. Please be sure you chair does not put holes in the football field. If the field is too soft, we wil ask that you not put chairs on it. Both home and visitor bleachers will be available as well as the grass areas near the concession stand.
If Nowata County, The City of Nowata or the State of Oklahoma impose new restrictions due to COVID-19 they will be implimented. We hope that does not happen.
See you all June 12th.

post_text:
Posting for Nowata Little League:

Hey guys!! Football will be here before you know it! 🏈🏈🏈

There will be a sign up Tuesday June 2nd at the Jack Gordon park (by the fire station) @ 6pm.

The cost for tackle football will be $125 which will include your jersey and pants with pads(we will do a day for checking out helmets and shoulder pads).

We will be offering flag football this year! Pre k - 1st, the cost for this will be $35 and will include a flag shirt! (We will always provide the belt and flags for games/practice) We are so excited to be adding this for our littles! We will have some local teams that they will play so they will traveling some.

We will have a discount for families with multiple children playing.

We are so excited for this season.

Please remember when coming to sign ups to keep following CDC guidelines for social distancing.

￼

Nowata Elementary School is currently conducting a “Save My Place” for the upcoming school year, 20-21 full-day Pre K classes. The classes are taught by an Early Childhood Certified teacher and each class has a teaching assistant. Online enrollment will still need to be completed when available.

By law, children must be at least four years of age, but not older than 5 years of age, on or before September 1st of the enrollment year.

“Save My Place” applications are web-based and to be completed digitally. Compete online at www.npsok.org or call Nowata Elementary for assistance. The office number is 918-273-0771. Leave a message with your phone number and your call will be returned.

May 12 at 2:02 PM ·

SOPHOMORES: Deadline June 30th

Oklahoma’s Promise. This nationally recognized scholarship continues to help make college a reality for students who qualify. The final deadline for high school sophomores to submit their applications is June 30, 2020. An important message has been posted on the OKP website:

If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

shared_text:
Jennifer Martinico Prince is with Connor Freeman and 7 others.
April 18 at 6:28 PM ·

Saturday April 17th: THE SURPRISE!
Please read the whole thing
Sadly the end of this year did not quite go as planned. We were robbed of many things: The Beg/MS Band Festival, 1st/2nd Year Honor Band, OKWU Choir Festival, State Solo Ensemble for both Band and Choir, Our Spring Concert, Our Awards Banquet, Mini Band Camp, MS Graduation and HS Graduation. Every single one of us has felt a lost with the way school ended and unfortunately for some of us not only was it these huge moments of our musical journey but it was to be our last, our goodbye, our look how hard we worked over the past 6 years to get to this point. So at this time I would like to recognize our the Senior Members of our Band and Choir. I have put together A picture bio for each Senior and I ask that you please take the time to read each one. Share this post and please help me recognize these amazing Seniors who have worked so hard to help grow as well as accomplish huge success with our Band and Choir Program. WE LOVE YOU SENIORS!

We can't wait to see what you've been up to!

We have several more than I had anticipated signing up for packet pick up.

I have gathered help and we will change the pick-up plan, slightly. The times are the same, but we will have two tables outside.

The Kinder, 3rd, and 5th will pick up at the south table.

You will walk-up and give us the name, grade, and class of your student. We will give you their packets
.
Please no more than one at a table and practice social distancing of 6ft in your line.

YOU MAY PICK UP SIBLINGS PACKETS AT THE SAME TIME.

Middle School parents/guardians:
Good morning! I want to share recent decisions we have made regarding “Distance Learning”. First it begins April 6. Our teachers will contact their students either by email or by Google Classroom. Classes will be Monday and Wednesday English and Social Studies. Tuesday and Fridays Math and Science. Teachers will assign two assignments per week.
If you do not have internet access you need to call the main office, 918-273-1346. ASAP
We will make documents for those of you that need them but we MUST know who and how many that is.
Mr. Sexson is in the office each day from 9-11. Call if you have any questions. Stay safe and healthy.

post_text:
The Ironmen Tennis Team competed in Pryor today.

Dillon Barnes made his first ever jump to 1 singles.... after a grueling 2 1/2 hour come from behind victory over Collinsville, Dillon fell to Pryor in a 5-7 battle before capturing 3rd place with a straight set win over Lincoln Christian.

In Doubles action, Gabe Velasco and Skyler Stevens teamed up for their first ever tourney. After defeating Miami in straight sets, they fell to Wagoner in a super tie break 10-12 in semi final action, before defeating Lincoln Christian to capture 3rd place.

Christian Farris advanced to the consolation finals before falling to Pryor in a super tie breaker.

Jayden Bowman and Josiah Clark also picked up their first win in doubles action defeating Pryor.

The Lady Ironmen Tennis Team competed in the Jim Hollis Pryor Invitational today.

The tourney included teams from Collinsville, Miami, Pryor, Tahlequah, Grove, Nowata, Lincoln Christian and Wagoner.

In Doubles action, after a hard fought 8-10 super tie break loss to Pryor in semi-final play, Mackenzie Barnes and Morgan Hobbs captured 3rd Place with a 6-2, 7-5 victory over Lincoln Christian.

Also in doubles action, Aiden Thompson and Allysa Barnes advances to the Consolation finals with a straight set win over Tahlequah before falling to Wagoner in the consolation championship.

Macie Slocter in her first ever tournament action pulled off a thrilling 8-6 victory over Lincoln Christian

Congrats Ladies on a great showing!!

March 5 at 12:18 PM ·

Incoming 9th graders (current 8th graders) should have taken home a letter and appointment time to their parents this week. There is a short parent meeting on Monday, March 9th during P/T Conferences from 6:30 to 7:00 pm in the MS/HS Commons area. You will receive your enrollment packet and discuss what you can expect in high school. Students and parents are encouraged to attend. 8th graders will receive extra credit in some classes if they and a parent attend the meeting. Individual enrollment appointments are on March 24th (see your appt time). Parents are not required to attend but are encouraged to do so. Packets must be brought back that day or any day prior to that. Thank you and we look forward to having you at NHS next year!

post_text:
Congratulations to Nowata's VEX Robotics teams!!
Four of the five teams have qualified to make it to the State Championship in Catoosa on March 12th and 13th. They've qualified based on their highest skills scores during this season. Be sure to congratulate the kids, they are:
The only High School team we have:
Team 44044A - Prestige Worldwide: Connor Freeman, Natalie Scott, Austin Jackson, Savana Harris, Josh Herrera, Breauna Henson, Kylie Brunger
The Middle School teams that are going to state:
Team 44044B - Baby Yoda: Cole McAvoy, Mason Greathouse, Amelia Prince.
Team 4044C - Nowatabotics: Faith Branstetter, Michael Prince, Ben Morris, Kaiden Miller, Chelo Prince.
Team 44044D - Paralyzed Penguins: JJ Gipson, Jimmy Lewis, Jacob Forehand, Tytes Forehand.
Also please Congratulate the one Middle School team that missed qualifying for the State Championship by 1 point!
Team 44044E - Dream Crushers: Sariah Fike, Lynda Ortiz-Valez, Mashayla Brown.

post_text: At this time, your child will be assessed on the following skills: shape recognition, color recognition, number recognition, recognizes first name, names letters in name, writes name, and letter identification. The purpose of this pre-screening is to give the teacher an opportunity to meet the family and create a bond with the student as well as parents. It also gives exposure to the pre-k environment- making it less threatening and increasing the likelihood of a positive start. To make an appointment please contact the office 918 -273 – 0771. There will be some evening appointments available for working parents.

Congratulations to members of the Nowata HS and MS Choirs on a job well done at OSSAA Vocal Solo Ensemble Competition today.

Elizabeth Wright received a Superior Rating on her Alto Solo advancing her to state competition in April.

Receiving Excellent Ratings today were:

Leslie Randall on her Soprano Solo (HS)

Jeremy Petry on his Baritone Solo (HS)

Madison Murray and Elizabeth Wright on their Vocal duet. (HS)

Mattie Wright, Hannah Morris and Kamra Campbell on their vocal trio (HS)

Taylena Seely on her Soprano Solo (MS)

Jazmyn Ortiz-Velez and Fallyn Nicholas on their vocal duet (MS)

Congratulations once again!!!!

post_text: Scholarship info!
shared_text:
Sherry Wilson
February 4 at 2:41 PM ·

The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education assists in the administration of the Frances Koop Parsons/AT&T Pioneers Memorial Scholarship. This scholarship program was established through the AT&T Pioneers to assist Oklahoma students in obtaining their education goals. The recipients of this scholarship will receive a $1,000 cash award to be used at an eligible Oklahoma career technology center, two-year college, or four-year university. This scholarship is open to first-time freshmen with at least a 3.0 high school GPA whose family income does not exceed $75,000. The 2020-21 application is attached and must be postmarked on or before March 27, 2020. Please contact Linette McMurtrey, Scholarship Programs Coordinator, at 405-225-9131 if you have any questions.
Linette McMurtrey
Scholarship Programs Coordinator
Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education
655 Research Parkway, Suite 200
Oklahoma City, OK 73104
(405) 225-9131
Fax (405) 225-9392
Lmcmurtrey@osrhe.edu

See Ms. Wilson for a copy of the application

post_text: Mrs. Angelia Franke's Pre-Algebra students complete an OKC Thunder StatLab activity in class. Students calculated the effective field goal percentage (eFG%) which shows how effective a player is on the floor when he is taking shots from anywhere on the court. The eFG% shows the difference between a seasoned 3-point shooter and a player who mainly takes shots within the 2-point range. The students complete a monthly lab activity and are entered into a contest to win new laptops for the classroom and basketball shoes for themselves.
